cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on cache-enabled device-to-device (D2D) communications, which is a networking topic. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses probabilistic latent semantic analysis (pLSA) and expectation maximization (EM) algorithm to learn user preference, which are machine learning techniques. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with optimizing caching policy based on user preference, which is related to social and information networks. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper formulates an optimization problem to maximize the offloading probability, which is related to information theory. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses machine learning techniques to predict user preference, which is related to artificial intelligence.
